OL,3,CPoliticians risk 'destabilising'
OL,4,Chealth sector if St Pier not suspended
OL,6,FIn response to speaking to a Guardian
OL,7,Fjournalist about the safeguarding
OL,8,Fconcerns, Deputy St Pier stresses that
OL,9,Fhe only confirmed a series of facts,
OL,10,Fdescribing the recommendation to
OL,11,Fsuspend him as "extraordinary and
OL,12,Fdystopian".
OL,14,FHe argues that using the Code of
OL,15,FConduct to prevent elected officials
OL,16,Ffrom speaking to the media "undermined
OL,17,Fdemocracy".
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G6/9
